# API route prefix convention (V0.6.5+)

Every new HTTP surface added to this repo MUST live under exactly one of three top-level prefixes. The audience determines the prefix; pick the prefix first, design the handler second.

| Prefix                          | Audience                                              | Auth                                                                                                      | Examples                                                                                       |
| ------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `/api/v1/admin/**`              | System administrators                                 | `current_admin_user` FastAPI dependency (session-cookie based). Long-lived admin tokens deferred.         | `/api/v1/admin/words`, `/api/v1/admin/packs`, `/api/v1/admin/global-packs`, `/api/v1/admin/cron` |
| `/api/v1/public/**`             | Anonymous (any caller)                                | None. Vercel deployment-protection still gates preview deploys; production is fully public.              | `/api/v1/public/health`, `/api/v1/public/packs/latest.json`, `/api/v1/public/global-packs/latest.json`, future AB-flag manifests |
| `/api/v1/family/{family_id}/**` | Members of one family (parents + bound child devices) | Per-family auth (parent session OR child Bearer device-token belonging to `family_id`). Auth deferred until later version; for now, accept the path param as decorative. | `/api/v1/family/{family_id}/family-packs`, `/api/v1/family/{family_id}/inbox`, `/api/v1/family/{family_id}/account` |

## Rule of thumb

1. If the resource is per-family or per-device-bound â†’ `/api/v1/family/{family_id}/...`
2. Else, if it requires admin context (cross-tenant management, system content authoring) â†’ `/api/v1/admin/...`
3. Else, if it is anonymous-readable platform content â†’ `/api/v1/public/...`
4. Otherwise, **stop and discuss** â€” you probably haven't named the audience precisely.

## Web (HTML) pages mirror the same pattern

- `/admin/**` â€” system admin web shells (e.g. global-pack authoring UI in v0.6.6+).
- `/public/**` â€” anonymous landing pages (e.g. preview-urls dashboards).
- `/family/{family_id}/**` â€” parent web shell scoped to a family (`_` is a decorative placeholder on pre-login pages such as `/family/_/login`).

## Historical legacy URLs (removed)

Older docs and clients referred to `/api/v1/parent/**`, `/api/v1/child/**`, bare `/api/v1/health`, `/api/v1/packs/latest.json`, `/api/v1/preview-urls.json`, `/api/v1/auth/**` (admin), `/api/v1/pair/redeem`, and `/parent/**`. Those entrypoints are **not served anymore**; use the `admin`, `public`, `/api/v1/family/{family_id}/**`, and `/family/{family_id}/**` prefixes above. When you touch routing, update `docs/WordMagicGame_overall_spec.md` section 13 (route table + prefix convention) in the same change.

## Pre-login parent OTP

Parent email OTP JSON endpoints and sibling HTML forms live at `/api/v1/family/{family_id}/auth/*` and `/family/{family_id}/auth/*`. Until a session exists, callers use a decorative `family_id` such as `_` (see apex `/` â†’ `/family/_/login` in `server/app/main.py`).

## Enforcement

When adding a new `APIRouter(prefix=...)` line:

- The prefix MUST start with `/api/v1/admin`, `/api/v1/public`, or `/api/v1/family` (HTML routers: `/admin`, `/public`, or `/family`).
- Do not resurrect removed legacy prefixes for new work.
- Update [docs/WordMagicGame_overall_spec.md](docs/WordMagicGame_overall_spec.md) Â§13.3 (route table) and Â§13.7 (route prefix convention) in the same PR.

## When this rule does NOT apply

- Static asset paths served by Vercel (e.g. `/_next/...`, `/favicon.ico`).
- Vercel cron entrypoints under `/api/v1/admin/cron/*` already follow the rule.
- Internal `/__mock_state__/*` debug endpoints in `server/mock_ui_server.py` (test fixture only, not a production surface).
